file.content:
{
  description = "NixOS configuration";

  inputs = {
    nixpkgs.url = "github:nixos/nixpkgs/nixos-unstable";
    home-manager = {
      url = "github:nix-community/home-manager";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
    llm-agents = {
      url = "github:numtide/llm-agents.nix";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
    dms = {
      url = "github:AvengeMedia/DankMaterialShell/stable";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
    niri-flake = {
      url = "github:sodiboo/niri-flake";
    };
    zen-browser = {
      url = "github:0xc000022070/zen-browser-flake";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
    tmuxcc-src = {
      url = "github:nyanko3141592/tmuxcc";
      flake = false;
    };
    banto = {
      url = "github:ryo-morimoto/banto";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
    agenix = {
      url = "github:ryantm/agenix";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
    voxtype = {
      url = "github:peteonrails/voxtype";
    };
    moonbit-overlay = {
      url = "github:moonbit-community/moonbit-overlay";
      inputs.nixpkgs.follows = "nixpkgs";
    };
    starlintLinuxBin = {
      url = "https://github.com/mizchi/starlint/releases/latest/download/starlint-linux-x64.tar.gz";
      flake = false;
    };
    starlintDarwinArm64Bin = {
      url = "https://github.com/mizchi/starlint/releases/latest/download/starlint-macos-arm64.tar.gz";
      flake = false;
    };
  };

  outputs =
    {
      nixpkgs,
      home-manager,
      llm-agents,
      dms,
      niri-flake,
      zen-browser,
      tmuxcc-src,
      banto,
      agenix,
      voxtype,
      moonbit-overlay,
      starlintLinuxBin,
      starlintDarwinArm64Bin,
      ...
    }:
    let
      localOverlay = final: _prev: {
        vibe-kanban = final.callPackage ./packages/vibe-kanban.nix { };
        claude-squad = final.callPackage ./packages/claude-squad.nix { };
        tmuxcc = final.callPackage ./packages/tmuxcc.nix { inherit tmuxcc-src; };
        beacon = final.callPackage ./packages/beacon.nix { };
        entire = final.callPackage ./packages/entire.nix { };
        zen-browser = zen-browser.packages.${final.system}.default;
        starlint = final.callPackage ./packages/starlint.nix {
          inherit starlintLinuxBin starlintDarwinArm64Bin;
        };
      };
    in
    {
      nixosConfigurations.ryobox = nixpkgs.lib.nixosSystem {
        modules = [
          ./hosts/ryobox
          agenix.nixosModules.default
          banto.nixosModules.default
          home-manager.nixosModules.home-manager
          {
            nixpkgs.hostPlatform = "x86_64-linux";
            nixpkgs.overlays = [
              moonbit-overlay.overlays.default
              localOverlay
              llm-agents.overlays.default
            ];
            home-manager = {
              useGlobalPkgs = true;
              useUserPackages = true;
              users.ryo-morimoto = {
                imports = [
                  niri-flake.homeModules.config
                  dms.homeModules.dank-material-shell
                  dms.homeModules.niri
                  voxtype.homeManagerModules.default
                  ./home
                ];
              };
              extraSpecialArgs = {
                inherit dms voxtype;
              };
            };
          }
        ];
      };
    };
}

content.thinking:
I can see at lines 233-239 that `system.autoUpgrade` is already configured:

```nix
system.autoUpgrade = {
  enable = true;
  flake = "github:ryo-morimoto/dotfiles#ryobox";
  dates = "05:00";
  randomizedDelaySec = "45min";
  allowReboot = false;
};
```

This uses `system.autoUpgrade` which runs `nixos-rebuild switch` periodically using the flake from GitHub. However, the issue is that this fetches the flake from **GitHub** (`github:ryo-morimoto/dotfiles#ryobox`), which means it uses whatever `flake.lock` is committed to the repo. So if the user runs `nix flake update` locally but doesn't push the updated `flake.lock` to GitHub, the auto-upgrade won't pick up the new inputs.


The real problem is that `system.autoUpgrade` just rebuilds with the existing lock file from GitHub—it doesn't actually run `nix flake update` to refresh the inputs. While the `flags` option could theoretically pass `--update-input` arguments, there's likely a better approach to automatically update the flake inputs as part of the rebuild process. The `--refresh` flag won't help since it still relies on the committed lock file. Looking at what's actually available in newer Nix versions, I need to use `--override-input` flags or run `nix flake update` as a separate step before the rebuild.

Since the NixOS auto-upgrade module doesn't have a built-in way to update inputs when pointing to a remote flake, I could either set up a local flake with a separate `git pull` and `nix flake update` process, or create a custom systemd timer that pulls the latest changes, updates the flake inputs, commits the lock file, and then triggers the rebuild.

The user has already chosen the systemd timer approach, so I need to focus on that. The current setup has `system.autoUpgrade` pulling from the GitHub repo, but it's not running `nix flake update` to refresh the lock file before rebuilding—that's the missing piece I need to address.

I'll create a systemd timer that periodically updates the flake lock file and pushes it back to GitHub, so the existing autoUpgrade mechanism picks up the fresh dependencies. Alternatively, I could point autoUpgrade to the local repo and just keep that updated locally, which would be simpler since it skips the GitHub round-trip. I'm leaning toward a simpler approach: set up a separate systemd timer that runs `git pull`, `nix flake update`, and commits/pushes the lock file before the regular `system.autoUpgrade` kicks in, so GitHub always has the latest inputs when the upgrade runs.

Writing the NixOS module... I'm noticing a potential issue with the git push command—it'll need SSH authentication, which should be available through the user's SSH keys. I'm also realizing the flake update at 04:00 needs to run before the system's daily autoUpgrade at 05:00, and I should verify that the Persistent flag will handle missed runs correctly if the machine is powered down. , and then have `nixos-upgrade` depend on it
2. Or use `system.autoUpgrade` with the local path instead

Let me go with a simpler approach: modify the `system.autoUpgrade` to use the local flake path, and add a pre-upgrade script that does `git pull && nix flake update`.

Actually the simplest and most robust approach:

1. Keep `system.autoUpgrade` pointing to GitHub (it's clean and reproducible)
2. Add a separate timer that runs before the upgrade time to update flake.lock and push

Let me implement this. The timer runs at 04:00, the upgrade runs at 05:00. The 1-hour gap gives enough time for the flake update + push.

One concern: running as `ryo-morimoto` user for git operations makes sense for SSH keys, but `nix flake update` might need internet access anyway, so that should work fine. Let me write this up properly.

